31/01/2006
ATHENS, Greece -- Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis reaffirmed his country's support for the scheduled EU accession of Bulgaria and Romania in 2007, during a meeting with Bulgarian counterpart Sergey Stanishev in Athens on Monday (30 January). The two also expressed support for the EU integration of the Western Balkan states, as well as for a solution to the Kosovo problem.
Separately, Austrian Chancellor Wolfgang Schuessel confirmed that his country -- which currently presides over the EU -- backs Bulgaria and Romania's membership in the Union. The statement came during Romanian Prime Minister Calin Popescu Tariceanu's visit to Vienna Monday. 
Slovenian President Janez Drnovsek made a similar statement of support after he arrived for a two-day visit to Bucharest on Monday. During talks with Romanian counterpart Traian Basescu, Drnovsek also stressed that the EU enlargement process must continue. (Nine o'clock - 31/01/06; ANA, MPA, BNR, Romanian Government Web site - 30/01/06)
